  "prompt": "What does add on item on Amazon mean?",
  "response": "An \"Add-on Item\" on Amazon refers to a product that is often lower-priced and typically small in size, which can be shipped only when included in orders that reach a minimum spending threshold. This is usually $25 or more. The concept behind Add-on Items is to help Amazon manage shipping costs for smaller items by ensuring they are included with larger orders. When you see a product marked as an Add-on Item, it means you cannot purchase it by itself unless you meet the minimum order requirement.",
